# [Question] Custom error message for invalid type · Issue #386 · colinhacks/zod
created: 2021-04-07, last updated: 2026-04-18, [Read more](https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/issues/386)

I checked where the default messages come from.
The defaultErrorMap
And found one location where you can override it: ParseParams in .parse & .parseSafe
```
import * as z from 'zod';
import {defaultErrorMap} from 'zod/lib/src/defaultErrorMap';
// schema.parse works the same
schema.safeParse(data, {
errorMap: (error, _ctx) => {
if (error.code === z.ZodErrorCode.invalid_type) {
if (error.expected === 'string') {
return {message: 'custom message for invalid string'};
}
}
return defaultErrorMap(error, _ctx);
}
});
```
...
@akomm If you upgrade to Zod 3 you can just call `z.setErrorMap` anywhere and it will globally update the error map for all calls to `.parse/.safeParse` - no need to pass in the custom error map every time.

